Problem Statement

Design a Java application to calculate the area of different geometric shapes using method overloading. Create overloaded methods to calculate the area of a circle,
rectangle, and triangle. Display the calculated area for each shape.

class AreaCalculator {

    void calculateArea(double radius) {
        double area = 3.14 * radius * radius;
        System.out.println("Area of Circle : " + area);
    }

    void calculateArea(int length, int breadth) {
        int area = length * breadth;
        System.out.println("Area of Rectangle : " + area);
    }

    void calculateArea(int base, double height) {
        double area = 0.5 * base * height;
        System.out.println("Area of Triangle : " + area);
    }
}

public class AreaOverloading {

    public static void main(String[] args) {

        AreaCalculator obj = new AreaCalculator();

        obj.calculateArea(7.0);
        obj.calculateArea(20, 10);
        obj.calculateArea(15, 10.0);

    }
}
output

